---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Tutorials | Vincenzo Di Perna"
  description="Short tutorials and technical notes on blockchain systems, benchmarking, digital assets, and reproducible experimentation."
  sideBarActiveItemID="tutorials"
>
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Tutorials</h1>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-90">
      Short technical tutorials and notes on blockchain systems, benchmarking,
      digital assets, distributed infrastructures, and reproducible experimentation.
      This section is designed to explain complex topics in a practical and accessible way.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-5">Blockchain fundamentals</h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">What is a blockchain?</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Beginner</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            A short explanation of blocks, transactions, validation, consensus,
            and why distributed ledgers differ from traditional databases.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">Public vs permissioned blockchains</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Beginner</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            A practical comparison between open public networks and controlled
            permissioned infrastructures, with examples of where each model fits.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">Consensus in simple terms</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Intermediate</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            A compact guide to how distributed participants agree on the state of
            a ledger, and why consensus affects latency, throughput, and security.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">Transactions, finality, and latency</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Intermediate</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            A short tutorial on the difference between transaction submission,
            confirmation, finality, and the latency metrics used in blockchain evaluation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-5">Benchmarking & evaluation</h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">How to benchmark a blockchain</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary">Benchmarking</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            A practical overview of workloads, clients, validators, throughput,
            latency, repeated runs, and why experimental setup matters.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">Why network topology matters</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary">Systems</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            A short explanation of how latency, bandwidth, topology, and network
            emulation can influence blockchain performance and predictability.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">Repeatability vs predictability</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary">Methodology</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            A note on the difference between obtaining similar results under the
            same setup and predicting behavior across controlled conditions.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <h3 class="card-title">Energy efficiency in blockchain experiments</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary">Energy</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            A brief introduction to measuring and interpreting energy usage in
            blockchain experiments, including normalization and caveats.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">More tutorials coming soon</h2>
        <p>
          I will progressively expand this section with concise tutorials, practical
          examples, diagrams, and short explainers connected to blockchain systems,
          digital assets, benchmarking, and research engineering.
        </p>

        <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">
            Suggest a topic
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
